"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423231","HM Treasury","false","2015-10-29","<p>This is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), who are operationally independent from Government.</p><br /><p>The question has been passed on to the FCA. The FCA will reply directly to the honourable member by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p><br />","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","12882 ; 13001 ; 13002 ; 13004","2015-10-29T15:05:33.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423231/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423231/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423231/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-22","Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment the Government has made of the effect on consumers of the practice of insurers in signing customers up to automatic policy renewals without the option to opt-out; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","13003"
