"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423251","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-10-30","<p>We have made no such estimates as all these costs are matters for the councils concerned which will have considered such matters when giving their provisional agreement to the North East Devolution Deal, which in addition to establishing a North East regional mayor, will create an Investment Fund to support the North East, worth up to £1.5 billion, with an initial allocation of revenue funding for capital financing of £30 million a year for 30 years.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","13062 ; 13064","2015-10-30T14:44:33.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423251/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423251/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-22","Mayors: North East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made under what working assumptions of the potential annual running costs for the office of a North East regional mayor.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","13063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423252","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","true","2015-10-29","<p>UK Government has allocated £122 million for the two Scottish Superfast Broadband projects - the Highlands and Islands project and the Digital Scotland project, which covers the rest of Scotland. Following the completion of the current contracted projects by December 2017, superfast broadband coverage will be around 93% within the Digital Scotland project area.</p><p><ins class="ministerial">We estimate that 42,746 homes and businesses in Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill constituency will have superfast broadband available to them by the end of 2017.</ins></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-10-29T16:47:30.723Z","2015-10-29T17:06:21.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423252/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423252/answer","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423252/answer/previousversion/26623","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-10-22","Broadband: Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the planned date is for the roll-out of fibre broadband in (a) the Chryston area and (b) the constituency of Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","13006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423253","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-02","<p>I have had no such discussions. Policing outside of sports stadia is a matter for individual clubs and the local police to determine. My Department has responsibility for ensuring the safety of spectators inside of sports stadia.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-11-02T18:19:55.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423253/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423253/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-10-22","Merseyside Police: Football","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions he has had with the Home Secretary on the potential effects of changes in the Merseyside Police mounted division on that forces' capacity to police football matches at Anfield and Goodison Park.","false","Biography information for Steve Rotheram","Liverpool, Walton","Steve Rotheram","13093"
