"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423274","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-27","<p>Some 840 former local Afghan staff are eligible for the Ex Gratia Redundancy Scheme, of which nearly 500 are eligible for the relocation option. Of these, nearly 200 have already relocated to the UK along with their immediate families. A further 60 have been awarded visas and are due to relocate in the coming months. The remainder are either going through the visa application process or are yet to be made redundant.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-10-27T16:13:19.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423274/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423274/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/423274/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-22","Afghanistan: Interpreters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many locally employed Afghan interpreters who worked alongside the British Army have (a) approached the Government for help under the ex-gratia redundancy scheme and (b) been relocated to the UK under the ex-gratia redundancy scheme.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","13116"
