"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422879","HM Treasury","false","2015-10-27","<p>The Government provided an overall assessment of the impact of Summer Budget policies in <em>Impact on households: Distributional analysis to accompany Summer Budget 2015</em> available here:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf</a></p><br /><p>The government provided an additional impact assessment on request of the House of Lords Secondary Legislation Scrutiny Committee. This can be found on the Committee’s web site at</p><p>http://www.parliament.uk/documents/lords-committees/Secondary-Legislation-Scrutiny-Committee/DraftTaxCreditsRegs2015-ImpactAssessment.pdf</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-10-27T16:04:33.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422879/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422879/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422879/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-21","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of changes to tax credits on family incomes.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","12916"
