"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422997","Home Office","false","2015-11-10","<p>The number of prosecutions under Regulations 12 and 13 of the Accession (Immigration and Worker Authorisation) Regulations 2006, in each of the years the regulations were in force, 1 January 2007 to 31 December 2013, is shown in Table 1. The data in the table has been provided by the Ministry of Justice (MoJ) and is not held by the Home Office. MoJ Court Proceedings Database holds information on defendants proceeded against, found guilty and sentenced for criminal offences in England and Wales.</p><p>The Regulations only allowed for employees to be served with a Fixed Penalty Notices (FPNs) under Regulation 13. The sanction against employers under Regulation 12 was prosecution through the Courts. The Home Office does not hold Management Information for this period which would explain why the prosecution numbers are low. Management information in Table 2 shows the number of FPNs notified to the Home Office as having been served in each of the financial years the Accession (Immigration and Worker Authorisation) Regulations 2006 were in force.</p><p>The Home Office has no record of any Fixed Penalty Notices being issued to Croatian nationals working in breach of the Accession of Croatia (Immigration and Worker Authorisation) Regulations 2013. The Home Office has not issued any civil penalties to employers in respect of breaches of the Accession of Croatia (Immigration and Worker Authorisation) Regulations 2013.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","12753","2015-11-10T17:49:41.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422997/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422997/answer","Table 1-2 PQs 12752 & 12753.doc","Table 1-2 PQs 12752 & 12753.doc","Employees served with a Fixed Penalty Notice","Employees served with a Fixed Penalty Notice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422997/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422997/answer/previousversion/25715","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-21","Worker Registration Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many (a) prosecutions have taken place and (b) penalty notices have been issued under paragraphs (i) 13 and (ii) 12 of the Accession (Immigration and Worker Authorisation) Regulations 2006 in each year since those regulations entered into force.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart McDonald","12752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422998","Home Office","false","2015-11-10","<p>The number of prosecutions under Regulations 12 and 13 of the Accession (Immigration and Worker Authorisation) Regulations 2006, in each of the years the regulations were in force, 1 January 2007 to 31 December 2013, is shown in Table 1. The data in the table has been provided by the Ministry of Justice (MoJ) and is not held by the Home Office. MoJ Court Proceedings Database holds information on defendants proceeded against, found guilty and sentenced for criminal offences in England and Wales.</p><p>The Regulations only allowed for employees to be served with a Fixed Penalty Notices (FPNs) under Regulation 13. The sanction against employers under Regulation 12 was prosecution through the Courts. The Home Office does not hold Management Information for this period which would explain why the prosecution numbers are low. Management information in Table 2 shows the number of FPNs notified to the Home Office as having been served in each of the financial years the Accession (Immigration and Worker Authorisation) Regulations 2006 were in force.</p><p>The Home Office has no record of any Fixed Penalty Notices being issued to Croatian nationals working in breach of the Accession of Croatia (Immigration and Worker Authorisation) Regulations 2013. The Home Office has not issued any civil penalties to employers in respect of breaches of the Accession of Croatia (Immigration and Worker Authorisation) Regulations 2013.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","12752","2015-11-10T17:49:42.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422998/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422998/answer","Table 1-2 PQs 12752 & 12753.doc","Table 1-2 PQs 12752 & 12753.doc","Employees served with a Fixed Penalty Notice","Employees served with a Fixed Penalty Notice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/422998/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","h